article.headline: Austin Peay 77, Tennessee Tech 70
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Drake Reed scored 21 points, leading Austin Peay to a 77-70 win over Tennessee Tech on Saturday night. The Governors (2-3, 1-0 Ohio Valley) never lost the lead after a Landon Shipley layup put them ahead 14-13 with 12:28 left in the first half. Derek Wright had 17 points and Shipley added 13 for Austin Peay, which shot 51 percent from the field and held Tennessee Tech (3-3, 0-1) to 39 percent shooting. Anthony Fisher scored 25 of his career-high 35 points in the second half, including nine straight to pull the Golden Eagles back from a 12-point deficit. His seventh and final 3-pointer of the night with 36 seconds remaining brought Tennessee Tech to within three points, 71-68. But a series of Tennessee Tech fouls combined with four free throws from Shipley, who went eight-of-11 from the line put the game out of reach. Jonathan Jones led Tennessee Tech rebounding with 10 and Fernandez Lockett grabbed nine rebounds for Austin Peay.
